<HEADLINE> Russia Expresses Concern Over CIS Border Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Tuesday voiced its
deep concern over the security of the southern border of the
Commonwealth of Independent States which is threatened by the
spreading civil war in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the Russian Foreign Ministry said that Russia
supports U.N. Security Council Resolution 1193 and will continue
its efforts to consult with various Afghanistan sides in seeking a
solution to the war.
</P>
<P>
Russia also called on the various sides to guarantee the safety
of international personnel while condemning Taliban's attack on
them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
