<HEADLINE> Japanese Emperor Meets Senior Chinese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Emperor Akihito and
Empress Michiko on Tuesday met Song Jian, vice chairman of the
Chinese Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Emperor Akihito expressed sympathy to the Chinese people struck
by floods and hoped disaster-hit Chinese residents could rebuild
their homes as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Song, who is also president of the China-Japan Friendship
Association, is attending the seventh Sino-Japanese
Non-Governmental Personages Council meeting in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Emperor Akihito wished success to the meeting, adding that the
two countries should make joint efforts to further develop
Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have to step up scientific and technological
cooperation, which would bring a better life to both peoples in
the future, the emperor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
