<HEADLINE> Annan to Chair Meeting on Congo (k) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DURBAN (South Africa), September 1 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary
General Kofi Annan will meet leaders of African countries to
discuss the Congo (k) conflict, South African Deputy President
Thabo Mbeki said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement at a press conference in the
International Convention Center in Durban where the Non-Aligned
Movement (NAM) conference is being held.
</P>
<P>
The secretary general is scheduled to arrive later Tuesday,
Mbeki told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He said that Annan will chair a crucial meeting of the
Southern African Development Community (SADC) to be held during
the NAM summit later this week, probably on Wednesday, to discuss
the Congo(k) problem.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will not only look at problems in the DRC, but
will also discuss the situation in Angola, According to South
African Deputy Foreign Affairs Minister Aziz Pahad.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki met Zimbabwean Foreign Minister Stan Mdenge on Monday
for about 50 minutes to discuss the DRC crisis.
</P>
<P>
Aziz Pahad said: "As chairman of the Southern African
Development Community and future chairman of the NAM, I think
South Africa is a good position to assist in getting a
co-ordinated approach to resolving this conflict."  
</P>
</TEXT>
