<HEADLINE> DRC Refugees in Tanzania Keeps Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The number of refugees
from the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) entering Tanzania to
flee fierce civil war continue to increase as 263 of them arrived
in the Kigoma region in the west Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This brings the number of refugees from DRC who have entered
Tanzania over the past four weeks to more than 2,000, said a
United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) officer in
Kigoma.
</P>
<P>
The officer, who preferred anonymity, clarified that all the
refugees are in good health and "none of them was injured."
</P>
<P>
He said UNHCR has everything for them in terms of food,
ommodations and treatment.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, UNHCR Kigoma sub-office head, J.F.Durieux, said all
refugees received are civilians and no rebellion soldiers are
among them.
</P>
<P>
The refugees crossed Lake Tanganyika by boat into Kigoma after
Tutsi-led rebels took up arms in Goma in the east of the DRC.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR has claimed that the influx of refugees is manageable,
as they are capable of handling even 1,000 new arrivals a day.
The refugees are taking shelter at Nyarugusu camp in the Kasulu
district. 
</P>
