<HEADLINE> Iran to Keep Troops Along Border with Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced on Tuesday to
keep the troops and equipment participating in the ongoing massive
military maneuver on the country's northeastern border with
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to local reporters on the sidelines of the maneuver in
Khorasan province, Commander of the Islamic Revolutionary Guards
Corps (IRGC) Yahya Rahim Safavi said the 70,000-strong troops and
equipment will remain in the region.
</P>
<P>
They are part of the Ashura-3 military games, which started
Tuesday morning along the border with Afghanistan amid heightened
tensions, according to the official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan Taliban militia, which now rules most of the
country, has been alleged to have kept in custody 11 Iranian
diplomats, a reporter and 35 truck drivers since its troops swept
into Mazar-e-Shrif, an opposition stronghold in northern
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran is seeking the release of the captured through diplomatic
channels, but it has threatened to exploit all possible means to
ensure their safe return home.
</P>
<P>
Keeping more troops along the border is seen as a move to put
more pressure on the Taliban, which accused the arrested Iranians
of providing weapons and amunitions to the opposition Northern
Alliance, headed by ousted President Burhanuddin Rabani.
</P>
<P>
Safavi revealed that some 110 long- and medium-range artillery
units and 152 armored tanks equipped with advanced equipment
including T-22-S would be involved in the war games.
</P>
<P>
He said the massive maneuver was aimed to preserve battle
readiness of the IRGC troops and Basij (volunteer) forces,
exercise and evaluate the capabilities of the IRGC's rapid
deployment forces in encountering any unprecedented crisis.
</P>
<P>
It was also designed to test the movement and flexibility of
the IRGC's different units in operational fields and in advancing
into 40 kilometers depth of a hypothetical enemy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Boosting security across the eastern borders against the
mischieves and prevention of drug trafficking are also among the
objectives of the war games, the commander added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
