<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, September 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin Wednesday issued a
decree instructing acting Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin to
form a government, said the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
In his decree, Yeltsin also reappointed six acting ministers
following a suggestion by Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
They are the acting Foreign Affairs Minister Yevgeny Primakov ,
the acting Justice Minister Pavel Krashennikov, the acting Defense
Minister Igor Sergeyev , the acting Deputy Premier in charge of
economy Boris Fyodorov, the acting Interior Minister Sergei
Stepashin and the acting Emergencies Minister Sergei Shoigu.
(Russia-Ministers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz warned on
Wednesday that Iraq will take further decisive actions to protect
its interests and security if the U.N. Security Council adopts a
hostile resolution against it.
</P>
<P>
Aziz was commenting in a statement on a draft resolution
submitted by the United States and Britain to the Security Council
proposing the council's review of sanctions on Iraq every 60 days
be suspended.
</P>
<P>
But he did not specify what steps Iraq would take if the
resolution is passed. (Iraq-UN-Draft Resolution)
</P>
