PHNOM PENH -- King Norodom Sihanouk decided Wednesday to hold a
five-party meeting on September 5-7 in Siem Reap in a hope to
defuse the current political crisis to some extent.
</P>
<P>
The King invited the three main political parties -- the ruling
Cambodian People's Party (CPP), the opposition Funcinpec and the
Sam Rainsy Party as well as the National Election Committee and
the Constitutional Council to participate in the meeting.
(Cambodia-King-Meeting)
</P>
