<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma on Wednesday passed a
resolution to urge acting Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin to
voluntarily reject the post of prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The resolution was passed 255-40 with no abstentions in the
lower house of parliament, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"Your voluntary rejection of the position of prime minister
could significantly reduce the tension and lead to a search for a
compromise," the document says. (Russia-Duma-Chernomyrdin)
