<HEADLINE> Flood-Stricken Areas Urged to Prepare for Onslaught of Winter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji has
called on governments in flood-stricken areas to make every effort
to help flood victims survive the coming winter.
</P>
<P>
Zhu conducted a fact-finding tour in disaster areas in
northeastern China from August 28-September 2. The premier said
efforts must concentrate on the construction of housing prior to
the arrival of winter.
</P>
<P>
He noted that people can raise funds themselves and either
obtain bank loans or donated funds. Local governments should also
subsidize housing construction.
</P>
<P>
Flood victims can either borrow grain from the government, or
trade labor for grain products. Flood victims will mainly depend
on donations for winter clothing, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu urged the Ministry of Civil Affairs to organize and
coordinate the transportation of winter goods and priority should
be given to flood-ravaged regions in northeastern China.
</P>
<P>
Temperatures in northeastern China have dropped to around 10
degrees Celsius at night and the onslaught of winter arrives in
less than a month.
</P>
<P>
The premier visited counties which sustained heavy damage
during the severe flooding. He also visited people living in tents
and makeshift shelters and encouraged them to employ self-reliance
when reconstructing.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also urged concerned departments to stockpile adequate
supplies of seeds, chemical fertilizers and pesticides to support
winter and spring cultivation in disaster-stricken areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
