<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Directs Chernomyrdin to Form New Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, Sept 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Wednesday issued a decree instructing acting Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin to form a government, said the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
In his decree, Yeltsin also reappointed six acting ministers
following a suggestion by Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
They are the acting Foreign Affairs Minister Yevgeny Primakov ,
the acting Justice Minister Pavel Krashennikov, the acting Defense
Minister Igor Sergeyev , the acting Deputy Premier in charge of
economy Boris Fyodorov, the acting Interior Minister Sergei
Stepashin and the acting Emergencies Minister Sergei Shoigu.
</P>
<P>
The move aims to "provide a durable functioning of the system
of running the country and continuity in implementing external and
defence policy, maintaining law and order and overcoming the
crisis," the press here quoted the decree as saying.
</P>
<P>
A Kremlin spokeswoman said the six would keep their jobs at
least until a new government is confirmed in office.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma has decided to take the second vote on
Chernomyrdin's premiership nomination on Friday. 
</P>
