<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Resolution to Promote Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The seventh meeting of
chairman and vice-chairmen of the Ninth National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference today
adopted a seven-point resolution to support reconstruction efforts
in flood-ravaged regions.
</P>
<P>
The resolution calls for a five percent cut in this year's
administrative expenditure for CPPCC National Committee
departments.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee will further concentrate financial
resources on reconstruction by cancelling national meetings
between now and the end of the year, with the sole exception of
the Standing Committee meeting required by CPPCC Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Fact-finding trips to disaster areas will be cancelled in order
to reduce burdens of local governments, and strict limits will
apply to foreign trips.
</P>
<P>
The resolution also calls for scholars and experts in CPPCC
local organizations to submit suggestions for reconstruction and
flood control. Local CPPCC committees have been instructed to
continue fund-raising activities in order to assist flood victims.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of CPPCC National Committee, presided over
today's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
