<HEADLINE> Simultaneous Raids on Child Porn Ring Conducted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Police in 21 countries conducted
simultaneous raids Wednesday on a suspected child porn ring which
has exchanged pornographic pictures of children over the Internet,
German police said.
</P>
<P>
The operation, coordinated by the British police authorities
via the Interpol, started at 0400 GMT across European countries
including Germany, Britain and France, as well the United States
and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The raids followed investigations in Britain which pointed to
over 180 individuals suspected of exchanging a large quantity of
child pornographic pictures over an Internet "chat room," the
German Federal Criminal Agency in Wiesbaden said.
</P>
<P>
German press reports quoted the British police authorities as
saying that more than 100,000 pornographic pictures had been
seized and dozens of suspects detained in the international
swoop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
