<HEADLINE> Oxfam HK to Release Emergency Relief to Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Oxfam Hong Kong, an
international development and relief agency, announced Wednesday
that it will be supporting emergency relief projects with flood
victims in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The assistance, which amounts to 5.5 million HK dollars (0.71
million U.S. dollars), will include food, water supplies, water
purifiers, sanitation equipment, fodder and vaccination for
livestock, rice seedlings and materials for tube wells, latrines,
and temporary housing.
</P>
<P>
Several search and rescue teams will be dispatched to affected
areas, and health teams will give special attention to pregnant
women, newborn babies and lactating mothers, an Oxfam Hong Kong
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
As of late August, the official death toll in Bangladesh has
risen to 500 while two-thirds of the country being flooded.
</P>
