Siem Reap in a hope to defuse the current political crisis to some
extent.
</P>
<P>
The King invited the three main political parties -- the ruling
Cambodian People's Party (CPP), the opposition Funcinpec and the Sam
Rainsy Party as well as the National Election Committee and the
Constitutional Council to participate in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Funcinpec Party expressed its gratitude for the invitation
saying it "fully supports the King's initiative to find solutions
to the current problems." The Sam Rainsy Party has not made any
comment yet.
</P>
<P>
Funcinpec has decided to send Tol Lah and other two members to
the meeting while Hun Sen, Chea Sim and another CPP member who are
already in Siem Reap are expected to be present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia began facing serious political crisis when the two
main opposition parties boycotted the recent election results and
refused to form a coalition government with Hun Sen as premier.
</P>
