<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Susanthika Jayasinghe of Sri
Lanka said on Wednesday that she will skip the Commonwealth Games
although she had been cleared of drug allegations.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe, 22, whose suspension was lifted last week by IAAF,
said she was not in a proper mood to compete at the Games slated
for September 11 in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
