endurance. This is because I am not yet in a proper mental state
to compete," said Jayasinghe.
</P>
<P>
However, she said she will be ready to compete in the Asian
Games in Bangkok in December.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe sprang to fame after winning the silver medal in
the women's 200 meters at last year's World Championships in
Athens, but was plunged into a doping scandal after a random test
in March.
</P>
<P>
She accused a top ministry official of spiking her urine
sample with banned steroids after she refused his sexual advances
and the IAAF lifted the suspension in late August. 
