<HEADLINE> Influential Tycoon Predicts Yeltsin Ouster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 2 (Xinhua) -- An influential Russian tycoon
said Wednesday that President Boris Yeltsin would have to resign
if the country had no strong political power.
</P>
<P>
Boris Berezovsky told the local Ekho Moskvy radio that Yeltsin
would have to step down to "make space for strong power."
</P>
<P>
However, Berezovsky, who is also executive secretary of the
Commonwealth of Independent States, said if strong power emerges
in Russia, Yeltsin may continue his presidency.
</P>
<P>
"Strong power will reconcile itself with the fact that the
president cannot be to a necessary extent involved in the
stormily developing events," he said.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a poll taken over the weekend shows
that 36 percent Moscow residents supports the voluntary
resignation of Yeltsin, though 28 percent viewed such a turn of
events as dangerous.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey of 936 Muscovites conducted by the
Public Opinion Fund on August 29-30, 56 percent of the respondents
support the idea of limiting the powers of the president. 
</P>
