<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Projects which have secured
financial back-ups should get priority in the action program of
the Southern African Development Community (SADC), an Angolan
official urged here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Idalina Valente, Deputy Minister of Planning, said at a forum
on the revision of the SADC action program that projects which
are beneficiary to the regional economy should enjoy priority in
the regional group's agenda.
</P>
<P>
Valente said that SADC should reduce the number of projects in
the action program and develop projects that are feasible, adding
that she would take the stance to the SADC summit to be held in
Mauritius on September 13 and 14.
</P>
<P>
SADC policy and programs should be balanced, mutual-beneficial
and conducive in conlidating trust among its member nations,
she said.
</P>
<P>
Its current action program, which covers about 400 projects
with an investment value at eight billion U.S. Dollars, were
passed on the Council of Ministers meetings in 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
About 75 to 80 percent of the money for the projects are
waiting for financial aid from international institutions.
</P>
