<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Sees Summer Traffic Surge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Both passenger and cargo traffic in
the Macao International Airport during the summer traffic peak in July
and August set new records, according to a news release issued by the
airport on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 241,140 passengers used the airport in August, easily
beating July's record of 205,595 and bringing about an increase of 35
over August 1997.
</P>
<P>
Passenger traffic grew strong especially on the air routes leading
to Taiwan and the mainland areas of China, compensating for losses on
North and South East Asian routes as a result of the Asian economic
crisis.
</P>
<P>
In July and August, passenger traffic increased 27 percent over the
same period last year. And the airport handled 16,078 tons of cargo, a
sharp increase of 124 percent over that in last year.
</P>
<P>
There are 13 regular airlines linking Macao with 25 cities, 13 of
which are in the mainland of China. Since its opening on November 9,
1995, the airport has handled 4.75 million passengers and 110,370 tons
of cargo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
