<HEADLINE> Six Cities Bid for 2006 Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Six cities have formally
submitted their applications to the International Olympic
Committee to bid for the hosting of the 2006 Olympic Winter Games
before Tuesday's deadline.
</P>
<P>
The bidders were Sion of Switzerland, Turin of Italy, Helsinki
of Finland which was in combination with Lillehammer of Norway,
Zakopane of Poland, Poprad Tatry of Slovakia, and Austria's
Klagenfurt, which is fronting a three-country effort with centres
in Slovenia and Italy.
</P>
<P>
Sion, the southern Swiss city which failed in earlier bids to
secure the 1976 and 2002 Winter Games, is widely seen as the
early front-runner for 2006.
</P>
<P>
An IOC evaluation committee will review the proposals and
visit all the candidate venues between October and November
before filing a report to the IOC executive committee.
</P>
<P>
A final decision will be taken by the IOC in Seoul on June 19
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
