<HEADLINE> China, Kazakhstan Win in Asian Handball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China scored a hard-fought
victory over hosts Japan 20-19 for its second win in three
matches in the Asian Junior Women's Handball Championships in
Osaka on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese, who will host the World Junior Championships next
year, took a narrow 9-8 lead at half time and held on to the
victory.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan, competing in the Asian championships for the first
time, also scored its second win against one defeat by beating
Chinese Taipei 24-16.
</P>
<P>
Four-time defending champions South Korea had a rest day after
wining its first two games to collect four points.
</P>
<P>
China and Kazakhstan also gained four points each, while Japan
and Chinese Taipei were still to win their first games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
