<DOCNO> XIE19980902.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Protection of Taiwan Investment not Affected: Article (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article noted that developing economic and trade relations
across the straits and encouraging investment from Taiwan is a
consistent policy of the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
As a result of this policy, the Chinese mainland has always
made efforts to improve the investment environment and protect
Taiwan businessmen's legitimate rights and interests according to
related regulations and laws.
</P>
<P>
There are some in Taiwan who take economic and trade activities
across the straits as bargaining chips in political lawsuits, the
article says.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, however, many Taiwan businessmen expressed their
confidence in mainland investment immediately after this case came
to their attention, it added.
</P>
<P>
Many businessmen also hope that Taiwan authorities give up
making use of so-called Taiwan businessmen to collect
intelligence, so as to retain the good reputations of legitimate
Taiwan businessmen, the article says.
</P>
<P>
According to related laws, the hearing of espionage cases,
unlike criminal cases, is not open to the public because these
cases involve state secrets, the article points out.
</P>
<P>
But taking people's concerns into consideration, some
authoritative departments publish accounts of these cases in a
timely fashion within the limits of the law, it says.
</P>
<P>
The article says that court-appointed lawyers entered pleas for
the accused, and helped contact their families to inform them of
the case and the situation of the accused after the Beijing
Municipal No. 1 Intermediate People's Court made its ruling of
first instance.
</P>
<P>
The article concludes that the proper rights and interests of
the four accused were fullly protected during the entire
litigation procedure.
</P>
<P>
The view of some in Taiwan that "the legal justice of all
procedure is suspected" shows a lack of basic legal knowledge and
basic facts, the article emphasizes.
</P>
<P>
The article calls for a clear awareness on the part of the
Taiwan people that espionage activities directed by the Taiwan
Military Intelligence Bureau indicate that the actions of the
Taiwan authorities are not in keeping with its promises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
