<HEADLINE> Share Prices Inch Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices inched up in
active trading on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as the
benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 4.52 points to end at
827.85 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 242 55 million units worth 244.62
million Singapore dollars (about 140.59 million U.S. dollars).
There were 210 losers against 96 gainers with 280 counters
unchanged
</P>
<P>
ChewEuHock was the most active stock of the day as it ended on
a turnover of 18.83 million stocks. It was followed by SingTel
that had 14.53 million units traded. M Res was next with 11.54
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH was the top gainer of the day as it rose by 1.30 Singapore
dollars to close at 13.50 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 was up 80
cents to finish at 16.90 Singapore dollars. Both UOB F and Venture
edged up 22 cents and closed 4.10 and 4.52 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the down side, GE Life was the biggest loser of the day as
it lost 60 cents to end at 7.00 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem slid
by 45 cents to close at 6.05 Singapore dollars. RothmansI shed 30
cents to finish at 6.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said Wall Street's overnight rise encouraged the market
and the firmer trend in Kuala Lumpur also boosted local buying
sentiment.
</P>
<P>
However, most investors were still cautious as they weighed the
effects of the foreign exchange controls announced by the Malaysia
government, dealers noted.
</P>
<P>
The market remained dominated by concerns that the upward trend
can not be sustained under the current volatile environment.
</P>
