Mindanao in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Imelda Banganan of the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and
Seismology said the jolt occurred at about 4:38 p.m. and its
epicenter was under sea some 140 kilometers off Mati, Davao
Oriental province.
</P>
<P>
Banganan said the quake was caused by the movement of the fault
zone in the Mindanao Sea and was felt in other areas in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
He said no damage and casualties have been found in the quake
but aftershocks are expected. 
