<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The first Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) Tropical Photobiology Workshop
opened in Ujungpandang, capital of Indonesia's South Sulawesi
Province Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is held with a view to establishing an ASEAN
Photobiology Association, introducing it to other Photobiology
associations, and creating a mutually beneficial cooperation on
the regional and international levels in the area of scientific
photos.
</P>
<P>
In his address, health minister's staff member Hadi M. Abednego
said Photobiology could be used to improve man's living standards,
particularly in the medical field.
</P>
<P>
However, the fruits of progress in medical technology must be
tightly selected to give the greatest benefit to the Indonesian
community, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Association of International photobiology president Pill
Soon Song said in his welcome address that photobiology is widely
applied in various disciplines, such as in the medical and
agricultural sciences, even in Southeast Asia's developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
The six-day workshop was organized by the Hasanuddin University
in Ujungpandang, the European Society of Photobiology and the
Association of International Photobiology.
</P>
<P>
It was attended by delegates from member countries of the
ASEAN, India, Japan, South Korea, Australia, the United States and
some European and African countries, according to Antara News
Agency Wednesday.
</P>
