<HEADLINE> Western China Trade Fair Ends with Best-Ever Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The shift of focus for China's
economic development from the eastern to the western part of the
country had an impact on one of the largest annual trade fairs,
held in this capital of Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
The sixth fair of its kind, and the largest ever, attracted
5,000 businesspeople from at home and abroad. When the five-day
event ended on August 30, some 59 letters of intent were signed
involving a total investment of 7.48 billion yuan, breaking the
5.4 billion-yuan record of last year.
</P>
<P>
The trading of property rights, which was for the first time
offered as the fair's theme, proved to be a success with 2.1
billion yuan of business accomplished.
</P>
<P>
The largest property transaction was the purchase of two
State-owned textile factories by a Taiwan company at a price of
500 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Commodity transactions, a traditional item at the fair, also
reached the new high of 2.2 billion yuan. 
</P>
