<HEADLINE> URGENT  Mongolian Parliament Rejects PM Nomination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Great Hural
(parliament) of Mongolia Wednesday vetoed the nomination of
Renchinnyamin Amarjargal as the country's prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hural then asked the ruling coalition of the National
Democratic Party and Social Democratic Party to submit a new
premier nominee to the parliament in 14 days after they discuss
the nomination with President Nachagyn Bagabandy, according to the
parliamentary press office. 
</P>
