<HEADLINE> Fujian's First Flowers Wholesale Market Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The first wholesale flowers and
plants market in southeast China's Fujian Province began
operations over the weekend in the coastal city of Zhangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the Minnan Flowers and Plants Wholesale
Market includes 110 nurseries.
</P>
<P>
The market, whose second and third phase are yet to be
constructed, has a planned area of 40 hectares and 800 nurseries.
</P>
<P>
In Zhangzhou, there are 63 joint venture flowers and plants
firms, which have invested 135 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city's flower acreage has exceeded 1,660 hectares, with
annual output exceeding 300 million yuan. Flowers are sold both at
home and abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
