<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exclusive Marketing Rights to Refrigerant Auctioned in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing-based Read Real
Estate Company has bought the exclusive marketing rights to the
refrigerant produced by multinational Greencool Group at a cost of
74 million yuan (about 8.915 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The real estate company will set up a joint venture in Shenzhen
with Greencool for the exclusive sales of the product in the
Shenzhen Special Economic Zone, according to a Read spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The price of the deal, struck at an auction in Shenzhen on
Tuesday, is said to be the highest ever for product marketing
rights in China.
</P>
<P>
Greencool, which is one of the world's largest refrigerant
producers, has two manufacturing enterprises in the world, one in
Britain and the other in Tianjin, each with an annual production
capacity of 30,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The environmentally friendly Greencool refrigerant was listed
by the State General Administration of Environmental Protection in
April as one of the best environmental protection technologies in
China. It is the only refrigerant on the list.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen was chosen as a major marketing target because it is
one of the largest refrigerant consumers in China, a Greencool
source said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
