<HEADLINE> ARATS Sends Letter to SEF on Behavior of Taiwan Reporter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Association for Relations
across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) today sent a letter to the
Taiwan Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) about a Taiwan reporter's
acts against the Security Law of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The letter said Taiwan reporter Lee Fu-chung violated the
stipulation of Article Eight of the Security Law of China while
reporting in Urumqi, capital of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The related department summoned him for interrogation at 11:00
p.m. on August 31 and told him his actions had violated the law,
the letter said, adding that Lee expressed regrets for his acts.
</P>
<P>
At about 2:OO a.m. on September 1, the department completed its
report on Lee, and Lee was premitted to continue his normal news
coverage on China's mainland, the letter said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
