<HEADLINE> Northeast China Company to Export 3 Million Bicycles to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sportsman Group based in
Anshan in northeast China's Liaoning Province will export
three million bicycles to the United States over the next
five years.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that a contract was signed early last month
at the International Grand Hotel in Anshan between the Sportsman
Group and the Kent Company of the United States, and the contract
signing ceremony was attended by local and central government
officials.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, the American company will be
responsible for marketing the bicycles in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The exported bicycles, with the brand name "Sportsman," will
have a combined value of 122 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Sportsman Group is one of China's leading bicycle
manufacturers and one of the first group enterprises, which has
been approved to export bicycles independently.  
</P>
</TEXT>
