<HEADLINE> Spanish Skipper Takes Lead in Soling World Champ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Calafat, 41st in the world rankings, is the only skipper to
have finished in the top 10 in all three heats sailed over the
first two days of the 10-race championship on Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Plagued by light winds, the championship has made a slow start
but Calafat has put sixth, second and fifth places on the
scoreboard to hold a lead of nearly 20 points.
</P>
<P>
He has 24 points. The next three boats on the leaderboard are
very tightly bunched, with Ukraine's Sergei Pichugin and American
Tony Rey sharing 43 points and Swede Per Ahlby on 43.7.
</P>
<P>
With an entry of 67 crews from 25 countries, the line-up of
former world champions and Olympic medallists shows there is some
serious competition in this three-man keelboat competition for
places at the 2000 Olympic Games in Sydney. 
</P>
