<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops Large Capacity Oil Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China has completed
construction of its largest crude oil distillation equipment
which became operational recently at the Maoming Petrochemical
Corp. in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
This equipment, with an annual production capacity of five
million tons, employs eight new technologies and was developed by
two companies attached to Tianjin University and the Maoming
Petrochemical Company.
</P>
<P>
With this operating, China has achieved an advanced level in
the application of container technology research in the field of
chemical-separating engineering, said an engineer responsible for
the development of the advanced equipment.
</P>
<P>
This project, at a cost of over 300 million yuan, will help
boost the Maoming Corporation's annual oil refining capacity from
8.5 million tons to 13.5 million tons, making it the first oil
refining facility in China with a combined capacity of over 10
million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
