<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Recovers Multi-Million Dollars in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Anti-corruption
Department (ACD) has recovered 40 million Jordanian dinars (about
56 million U.S. dollars) since its establishment in 1996, the
semi-official Jordan Times reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ACD, taking charge of investigation into embezzlement,
forgery, smuggling and illegal marketing activities, had broken
605 cases by the end of June and nabbed 336 offenders, Minister of
Information Nasir Judeh said.
</P>
<P>
Smuggling accounted for the biggest proportion among the cases
and the smuggled items ranged from telephone sets, satellite
receivers, facsimile machines, watches to foreign currencies,
Judeh said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
