<HEADLINE> Beijing-Taiwan Cultural Exchanges Flourish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing and Taiwan held in 14
cultural exchange activities in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Fifty Beijing artists visited Taiwan and staged two
performances of Quju, a local opera derived from ballad singing,
and were warmly received by audience on the island.
</P>
<P>
A group of 12 Beijing advertising professionals visited many
media organizations and ad companies in Taiwan and conducted
academic exchanges with their Taiwan counterparts.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, eight Taiwan artists came to Beijing to
attend a performance of Kunqu Opera and conducted cultural
exchanges with actors and actresses of the Beijing Kunqu Troupe.
</P>
<P>
Nong Wang, a famous Taiwan painter, played host to an
exhibition of Chinese painting at the Xu Beihong Museum in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
One Beijing cultural official said that during the second half
of this year, the city will send the Children's Peking Opera
Troupe and the Beijing Modern Dance Troupe to perform and lecture
on culture and art in Taiwan.  
