<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stock Exchange Suspends Trading in Financially Troubled Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Stock Exchange
suspended trading Tuesday in Jiangsu Sanshan Industry and Commerce
Co. Ltd. The company has been losing money for three consecutive
years.
</P>
<P>
The move, the first suspension in the exchange's 10-year
history, represents a step toward strengthening market regulation
and reducing risks, market analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The company, mainly involved in chemical fiber production,
incurred verified losses in 1995, 1996 and 1997. According to
relevant regulations of the exchange and the country, trading must
be suspended if a company suffers losses for three consecutive
years. Trading can be resumed once the company begins to make
profits.
</P>
<P>
Since this spring, the exchange had rendered the status of
"Special Treatment" to 10 money-losing listed companies, including
Jiangsu Sanshan, reminding investors of the uncertain prospects of
these firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
