<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province now has 16,595 Internet subscribers, including 95
corporate users who rent special fiber-optic cables for greater
and easier access to the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Liaoning Provincial Digital
Telecommunications Bureau said that 9,500 subscribers have been
added in the first seven months of this year.
</P>
<P>
