the provincial pricing bureau, and the provincial administration
for industry and commerce, publish information on books, pricing,
and consumer complaints on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The province's port city of Dalian this summer organized a camp
where students received free training on the World Wide Web during
their holidays. Many newspapers have also started special pages
to popularize knowledge about the Internet and related fields.
</P>
<P>
Feng Qiang, an official with the province's Digital
Telecommunications Bureau, said his province will use Internet
services for long-distance education, medical care, and inquiries
into scores on national university and college entrance
examinations in the future.
</P>
<P>
China was first connected to the Internet in April 1994, and
now has 1.06 million Internet subscribers, said sources from China
Internet Information Center. 
