<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Former U.S. Secretaries of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said
here today that the common task ahead for China and the United
States is to make continuous efforts to assure healthy and stable
Sino-U.S. relations into the coming 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark while meeting with a U.S.-China Society
delegation led by Dr. Henry Kissinger and Cyrus Vance, both former
U.S. secretaries of state.
</P>
<P>
Jiang underlined that the recent improvement and growth of
Sino-U.S. ties is widely welcomed by the people of both countries
and has won positive comments worldwide.
</P>
<P>
"The good development momentum in the past year ushered
bilateral ties into a new phase," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to President Jiang, the joint decision he made with
U.S. President Bill Clinton during his U.S. visit last fall set
the direction and framework for the growth of bilateral ties. "We
all agreed to accelerate the pace of building such a partnership
and enhance exchanges and cooperation in wide-ranging fields
during President Clinton's China trip at my invitation," he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang welcomed the visit of the delegation. "I should give my
special welcome to Dr. Kissinger for his thirtieth China visit,"
the president said.
</P>
<P>
"Some 27 years have elapsed since your first China trip, and
Sino-U.S. ties have witnessed profound changes in that time,"
Jiang told Kissinger.
</P>
<P>
"Although we have seen some turns and twists, bilateral
relations in general move forward," he said, adding that such
development is in the fundamental interest of the two countries in
the long run, and is itself an irreversible necessity of history.
</P>
<P>
Jiang praised both Kissinger and Vance for their important
contributions in opening the gates of Sino-U.S. relations and the
normalization of bilateral ties, and hoped that they and other
friends continue efforts to improve Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also briefed the guests on China's efforts to combat the
torrential flooding occurring this summer.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger said the mutual visits paid by the leaders of the two
countries have brought bilateral ties into "the best period" in
recent years. He told Jiang that people in his country have
reached a wide consensus to develop ties with China, which are in
the interest of both countries.
</P>
<P>
He also appreciated China's responsible attitude during the
Asian financial crisis and expressed his sympathy for the
devastation of the recent serious flooding.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is visiting China at the invitation of the Chinese
People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.  
</P>
