<HEADLINE> Survey: China Serious about Public Security, Situation Disturbing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) - China's top legislature, the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), has
found in a recent survey that local governments are serious about
instituting a comprehensive public security mechanism in
communities and people feel safer today.
</P>
<P>
But the survey also revealed that the general security
situation is still worrisome and disturbing.
</P>
<P>
"The comprehensive management of public security is still a
long-term and arduous task, and governments at various levels
should never let up in their efforts," said Cao Zhi, vice-chairman
of the top lawmaking body, at a meeting concluding the survey.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee sent three teams in July to Hainan,
Jiangsu and Jilin provinces to look into how a law on public
security was enforced.
</P>
<P>
Seven local legislatures in other provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities have been authorized to conduct inspections in
areas under their jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
According to the checks, local governments are very interested
in establishing a system called "safer and civilized communities"
which mobilizes the public to help police. They pay equal
attention to crime prevention and crackdowns.
</P>
<P>
Cao said that, because of this system, localities are able to
safeguard the general stability of the society while deepening
reforms, opening up and maintaining sustained and rapid economic
growth.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
