<HEADLINE> Suspension of ProCQ%iBQ%=9J9*u+V,*Y5ected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government has
rejected a wholesale suspension of the privatization process as
demanded by Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The suspension will cause too much damage and cessation of
external donor funding, Wednesday's New Vision daily quoted a
senior official as saying.
 Xtthew Rukikaire, the Minister of State for Finance, told
Parliament Tuesday that the sale of some enterprises can be
temporarily halted, but the privatization process should continue
to proceed.
</P>
<P>
