<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Lanka Mapes Out 10-year Plan For Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's national carrier
Air Lanka has mapped out a dynamic ten-year strategy plan for the
future, according to airline sources here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In 20 years the airline which took off in September 1979, has
come a long way. The bold plan for its progress promise it will
soar to even greater heights in the future, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The airline entered into a partnership with Emirates Airlines
of the United Arab Republic on April 1st, this year. the ten year
plan has been mapped out designed to transform the airline into a
source of profit.
</P>
<P>
While Emirates has become Air Lanka's Business partner, its
role as the nation's international airline will not be diminished,
the sources pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Emirates has made a commitment to purchase a 40 percent stake
in Air Lanka. the first stage was the purchase of a 26 percent
shareholding, the balance of 14 percent is to be acquired by
Emirates in the next two years.
</P>
<P>
The partnership puts Air Lanka under Emirates management for
ten years. A new board of directors has been appointed recently.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the ten year strategy plan under the new
management was to transform it into an airline matching the best
in professionalism and retaining its own special Sri Lankan
identity.
</P>
<P>
The prime aim is to raise the profitable expansion of the
airline to the industry average of 14 percent without compromising
on safety or service.
</P>
<P>
Key components will be the restructuring of route networks and
schedules and the introduction of new aircraft, said the sources,
adding that In addition an investment of 12 million U.S. dollars
is to be made for the replacement of outdated information
technology equipment essential for the airlines operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
