<DOCNO> XIE19980902.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation in Latin America Stabilized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Economic Commission for
Latin America and the Caribbean (ECLA) Tuesday praised regional
countries for keeping inflation at a rate of about 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
In a report entitled "Economic Study of Latin America and the
Caribbean 1997-1998," the ECLA pointed out that the stability of
pricing was one of the regional countries' main economic
achievements.
</P>
<P>
It said that on an average, regional inflation fell from 18
percent in 1996, to about 10 percent in 1997, the second lowest in
half a century.
</P>
<P>
But inflation in the first half of this year increased
slightly, which does not mean a setback overshadowing what has
already been achieved, the report noted.
</P>
<P>
Most Latin American countries witnessed low inflation in 1997
and 1998. Out of 19 countries, 10 countries maintained a one-digit
inflation rate in both years. Seven countries stayed between 10-20
percent. Only Ecuador and Venezuela registered an inflated price
increase between 30-40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Inflationary pressures coming from the growing internal demand
could be stabilized, thanks to the important increase in foreign
demand. At the same time, labor force expansion has helped to
mitigate the increase in wages, the document adds.
</P>
<P>
The rise in inflation, or its suspension in some countries, may
be explained partially by the El Nino climate phenomenon, which
generated major losses in agriculture. As a consequence, there
were significant increases in the prices of some crops in high
demand.
</P>
<P>
There were also other factors influencing inflation, such as
the adjustment in public services prices, government regulations
and the devaluation of some currencies.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the reduction in the prices of some imports,
especially oil, has facilitated stabilization efforts, according
to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980902.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
