the Mekong River Commission Secretariat began full operations
Monday in Phnom Penh, Cambodia Daily reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After 41 years in Bangkok, the secretariat decided in 1996 to
rotate its headquarters every five years. The headquarters will
move to Vientiane, Laos, in 2003.
</P>
<P>
The office opened here in July, and since then, staff and
operations have been slowly transferred to Phnom Penh. Most of the
expatriate workers and staff from the region have decided to
continue working for the commission and have moved to Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
In addition, about 25 Cambodians will join the commission as
permanent employees, according to a statement from the office.
</P>
<P>
