<HEADLINE> Tamil Nadu To Prevent Infiltration Of Sri Lankan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Police of India's Southern
State of Tamil Nadu have launched a massive operation to prevent
Sri Lankan rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
from infiltrating the state.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here Wednesday, Indian
intelligence officers and police have already seized a dinghy
owned by the LTTE to smuggle goods.
</P>
<P>
The Indian police, who commenced search operations on Sunday,
have questioned several residents of the coastal belt regarding
the hideouts of LTTE militants.
</P>
<P>
In addition to having conducted a house to house search to
flush out LTTE cadres, the police have warned hotel owners not to
provide shelter to LTTE suspects, and have also made arrangements
to check all trains reaching Chennai from coastal areas in the
deep south of the country, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
It is said the LTTE leaders are due to attend a rally on
September 15 in south of India.
</P>
<P>
The India's Southern State of Tamil Nadu was a base of training
rebels of the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 15-year war against the Sri Lankan
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
