<HEADLINE> Italian Police Arrest 33 Mafia Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Italian police arrested 33
suspected Mafia members and confiscated a large amount of property
in the southern city of Reggio di Calabria on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the raid, codenamed Olympic No.4 and based on three
previous operations, 41 arrest warrants were granted, 33 people
arrested with eight still at large. Those arrested, including
lawyers and former government officials, allegedly belonging to a
Mafia organization known as Ndrangheta.
</P>
<P>
The seized property was valued at 260 billion lire (150 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the operation, police investigated more than 500 people, and
123 suspects are expected to go on trial by November 16. The
trials are expected to clear a series of crimes over the last 20
years.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the anti-Mafia committee of the Italian Parliament
O. Del Turco called Tuesday's raid a great victory in the
anti-Mafia campaign.
</P>
<P>
The Ndrangheta group, which stems from Calabria of southern
Italy, mainly deals with drug and arms trafficking and blackmail.
</P>
</TEXT>
