<HEADLINE> Italian Legislators Praise China's Tibet Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government's policy
toward Tibet has proved right and produced positive results, an
Italian legislator said on Tuesday after an 11-day visit by a
parliamentary delegation to the Chinese autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Renzo Gubert, chairman of the Italian Parliamentary Friendship
Association with China, said members of the delegation agreed
unanimously that the Chinese government has made positive
achievements in improving the infrastructure and preserving
cultural relics in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The government has also helped to improve the living standards
in Tibet and promote exchanges with other regions in China, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said the delegation saw a wide freedom of religious belief
and great efforts in protecting and maintaining the numerous
monasteries in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan language was being taught in schools, traditional
Tibetan medicine is practised while young Tibetan men are exempt
from military service, the statement noted.
</P>
<P>
China's one-child policy does not apply to Tibetans, who can
have two or more children, it said.
</P>
<P>
Tibetans now account for 70 percent of the employees in
administration departments, more than double the 30 percent in
1979, while non-Tibetans all return home after their working term
in Tibet expires, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The five-member Italian parliamentary delegation visited Tibet
between August 21 and 31 at the invitation of the Chinese
Association for International Understanding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
