<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's imports of luxury
goods in May 1998 recorded a sharp drop of 60.92 percent compared
to the same period last year, a government press release available
Wednesday said.
</P>
<P>
The import on 17 items of luxury goods in May 1998 has
decreased to 22.96 million U.S. dollars or by 24.88 percent from
April 1998, or 60.92 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Perfumes and cosmetics, camera and parts, lens, wool, foreign
liquor, and leather bag and belt are the six items on top of the
list of imported luxury goods in May.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, imports of clock and parts, wine, liquor, leather
shoes, fruits and flowers recorded sharpest decrease in May 1998
compared to the same month one year earlier, the press release
said.
</P>
<P>
After the break-out of the financial and economic crisis in
Thailand, the government has launched a series of campaigns,
encouraging people to reduce their use of imported luxuries and
turn to home-made products. 
