<HEADLINE> Myanmar Engineers to Undergo Training in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 16 engineers of the
Public Works of the Myanmar Ministry of Construction will receive
skill supervisory and technology instructor upgrading courses in
the Philippines under a memorandum of understanding (MOU) between
the two governments on human resources development.
</P>
