the nine-week training courses will be conducted at the Meralco
Foundation Institute, sponsored by the Philippine government.
</P>
<P>
The MOU was one of the four signed between the two governments
when Chairman of the Myanmar State Peace and Development Council
Senior-General Than Shwe paid a state visit to Manila in February
this year.
</P>
<P>
The four MOUs are on investment promotion and protection,
cultural cooperation, human resources development and mutual visa
exemption for diplomats and officials.
</P>
<P>
Both Myanmar and the Philippines are members of the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations. The exchanges and cooperation between
the two countries had increased since Chairman Than Shwe met
former Philippine President Fidel Ramos in Bangkok in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The latest visit of Chairman Than Shwe to Manila in February
has lead to further promotion of the two countries' bilateral
ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
