<HEADLINE> Bank Subsidiaries Mushroom in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Panama's financial system
registered a considerable rise in bank subsidiaries over the last
three years, according to the Superintendency on Banking and
Insurance (SBI).
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1995, there were 232 subsidiaries throughout the
country, the SBI said.
</P>
<P>
A year later, in 1996, subsidiaries of the principal banks
operating in Panama amounted to 242 and last year they reached 266.
</P>
<P>
The opening of bank subsidiaries was a "boom in Panama, having
appeared just like mushrooms after rain," said the report by the
institution that regulates banking in Panama.
</P>
<P>
The SBI attributed the rise to competitiveness among banks.
</P>
<P>
Panama's International Banking Center is made up of 104 banks
and employs 10,958 people, of whom 10,775 are Panamanians and 183
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
According to the SBI, Panama's banking system pays 130 million
U.S. dollars in salaries yearly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
