<HEADLINE> China Promotes Awareness of Fire Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale campaign for
promoting public awareness of fire control was launched across the
country yesterday to mark the implementation of the Fire Control
Law.
</P>
<P>
Today's China daily reported that the law was promulgated on
April 29 this year in the second session of the Standing Committee
of the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The campaign was arranged by the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Golden Shield Art Ensemble presented an evening
performance on the fire control law and was enthusiastically
received by audiences.
</P>
<P>
A competition questionnaire on knowledge about the law was
distributed nationwide last month and more than 10 million sheets
have been returned so far.
</P>
<P>
The ministry's Fire-Fighting Bureau said 69,574 blazes were
reported in the first half of this year, killing 1.095 people and
injurying 2,175.
</P>
<P>
The Yuquanying Roundabout Furniture Center in Beijing was
totally destroyed by a big fire this May and the disaster resulted
in 20.9 million yuan (2.52 million U.S. dollars) in economic
losses. The municipal government has taken the fire as an example
to promote activities publicizing the new law.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition on the fire damage in recent years opened in
Beijing yesterday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
