<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 00:00 GMT, September 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Visiting U.S. President Bill Clinton said Tuesday
that Washington will stick with Russians if they continue on the
reform course.
</P>
<P>
"Today's financial crisis does not require you to abandon your
march toward freedom and free markets," Clinton said in a speech
delivered at the Moscow Institute of Foreign Relations.
</P>
