<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The General Office of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee and the General Office of the State Council
yesterday issued a circular calling for frugal economic practices
during the ongoing flood control and relief effort.
</P>
<P>
The circular urged governments and departments at all levels to
practice thrift and eliminate waste in order to make greater
contributions to the nation's economic growth and capacity to help
more flood victims resume normal lives at the earliest possible
date.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese people are confident and capable of winning the
battle against the ongoing heavy flooding and of achieving the
goal set for this year's national economy, President Jiang Zemin
yesterday told former Japanese Prime Minister Toshiki Kaifu.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 20th anniversary of the China-Japan Peace
and Friendship Treaty.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Zhu Rongji yesterday called for accelerated efforts
to plant more trees to improve environment.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said torrential rains combined with abnormal weather
conditions have caused heavy flooding in both the southern and
northern parts of the nation.
</P>
<P>
However, according to Zhu, the disaster has, at least in part,
been due to rampant deforestation which led to serious erosion
and, in turn, silting.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, Tuesday affirmed the necessity for the Three
Gorges Dam Project and stressed that the hydropower project will
play a major role in reducing floods by the year 2003.
</P>
<P>
Li exchanged views with hydrologists and experts concerning
accelerated efforts to construct more water conservancy projects
following this year's wide-spread flooding.
</P>
<P>
-- Hu Jintao, president of the Central Party School of the
Communist Party of China, yesterday urged Party officials at all
levels to earnestly study Deng Xiaoping Theory and use it as a
guide for their work.
</P>
<P>
Hu addressed the opening ceremony for the fall semester and
noted that studying Deng Xiaoping Theory will help leading
officials acquire a better understanding of the Party's major
policies and in turn do a better job in deepening reforms and
promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China firmly opposes the United States' latest plan to sell
advanced weapons to Taiwan, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao
said yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- The Yangtze River's eight flood crest, gradually losing
strength as it progresses, passed the Jingjiang section without
incident at 4 pm yesterday.
</P>
<P>
-- This summer's floods have caused the government to expand
this year's investment in water conservancy to a record 35.8
billion yuan (US$4.3 billion).  
</P>
