<HEADLINE> Dini Says Europe Cannot Abandon Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Amid Russia's serious political
and economic crisis, Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said
Tuesday that Europe cannot abandon Russia in its hour of need
since Germany was not deserted after World War II.
</P>
<P>
At a conference attended by the country's 127 ambassadors, Dini
said Russia "will be a talking partner in the future." Without
Russia, the dialogue between the East and West would be less
fundamental and more difficult.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister also stressed the necessity of making the
Group of Eight (the West's seven industrialized nations plus
Russia) into a permanent "consultation mechanism" which would
enable the eight nations to achieve concerted action to avoid the
risk of a global recession.
</P>
<P>
The G8 should act as a "command bridge" between the East and
West, he added.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Dini also outlined Italy's foreign policy on
European integration, trans-Atlantic relations and its ties with
other Mediterranean countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
