<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States Returns Historic Chinese Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States has returned
47 historic relics to China, according to the customs service of
Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Most of the relics are pieces of pottery ware dating back to
the Han (206 B.C.-220), Tang (618-907) and Ming dynasties
(1368-1644).
</P>
<P>
An official with Tianjin Customs said that the relics were
seized in smuggling cases by the United States Customs Service,
which has returned an abundant amount of such smuggled historic
Chinese relics since China joined the Interpol in 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
