<HEADLINE> Machinery Firm Set up in the Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China National Technical
Import and Export Corp (CNTIC) yesterday launched a wholly-owned
subsidiary in the Philippines to assemble high-quality machinery
and electronics products, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The new company, which is named CNTIC (Philippines) Electrical
Products, has one million US dollars in registered capital. Total
investment is expected to be 3.6 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is financially backing the corporation
in establishing the subsidiary. The Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Co-operation (Moftec) has provided the corporation
investment.
</P>
<P>
The new company will market a variety of machinery and
electronics products, such as electrical fans, video compact disc
(VCD) players and microwave ovens, in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the company is expected to design and manufacture
different series of machinery and electronic products in the
Philippines for export to neighbouring countries and the rest of
the world.
</P>
<P>
As the leading technology import and export company in China,
CNTIC's foreign trade volume amounted to 3.09 billion US dollars
last year, which ranked fourth among all of China's foreign
traders.  
</P>
</TEXT>
