<HEADLINE> Charity Game Planned for Bomb Victim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Ireland and Northern Ireland
are planning to have a two-leg friendly football match to raise
money for victims of the Omagh tragedy.
</P>
<P>
"We are agreed in principle to holding the match," said
Football Association of Ireland (FAI) chief executive Bernard
O'Byrne on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
