the first match in Belfast and the second in Dublin.
</P>
<P>
The Gaelic Athletics Association has raised at least 215,000
Irish pounds (308,500 U.S. dollars) from ticket sales for
Saturday's All-Ireland hurling semi-final replay which it would
put towards its own fund for the Omagh bomb victims. 
