<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Graf, Novotna Win First Round Matches at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Five-time champion Steffi
Graf of Germany, making her first-ever appearance at the new
National Tennis Center, battled past promising young American
Corina Morariu 6-2, 3-6, 6-1 today in opening round match at the
U.S. Open tennis championships in New York.
</P>
<P>
Graf broke Morariu on her first two service games and appeared
o her way to an easy victory. But she began to misfire with
unforced errors in the second set and Morariu capitalized with
two breaks to take the set.
</P>
<P>
Graf regrouped in the third rubber, breaking Morariu early for
a 3-0 lead and broke again to go up 5-1. She wound up it out
when Morariu sent a backhand into the net. Graf had 31 winners
but committed 28 unforced errors in the 92 minute battle.
</P>
<P>
Graf missed last year's Open due to surgery and a variety of
ailments. She lost number one ranking during her long layoff and
took a major step in her comeback last week by winning the Pilot
Pen tournament. The victory moved her up to the No. 26. She is
seeded eighth at the Open due to a special exemption from the WTA
Tour,and it is her lowest seeding since 1985.
</P>
<P>
Graf beat number two Lindsay Davenport of the United States
and number three Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic in the Pilot
Pen for her first victories over top 10 players since May 1997.
</P>
<P>
Novotna, the Wimbledon champion who is seeded third, beat
Jennifer Capriati of the United States 6-4, 6-3. Novotna
overtook Davenport to rank second in the world yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Conchita Martinez of Spain routed Miriam Oremans
of the Netherlands 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Davenport and French Open champion Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of
Spain are fighting their rivals this evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
