<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boxing Champion Charges Dropped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A judge has dismissed two
charges of assault against the world boxing champion Herbie Hide
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The case was halted after one of the men who said he had been
attacked failed to appear at Norwich Crown Court to give evidence.
</P>
<P>
Hide, 27, from Norwich, had denied assulting the coaches while
training for a fight in a gym in the city in March 1997.
</P>
<P>
Judge David Mellor formally dropped the charges of assault
occasioning actual bodily harm.
</P>
<P>
He ruled that the absence of a key witness would make it
impossible for the Nigerian-born Hide to receive a fair trial.
</P>
<P>
Hide, who claimed he was the victim of a 30,000 Pounds
blackmail plot, said he was "very pleased" with the outcome.
</P>
<P>
The prosecution claimed Hide had attacked Allister Drummond
and Chris Johnson at the Norwich Lads Club after one of them
asked him to turn down the volume on his "ghetto blaster".
</P>
<P>
Hide was sharing the gym with a number of young amateurs who
were under the wing of Drummond and Johnson.
</P>
<P>
Hide said he had given Drummond nothing more than a "playful
tap",but Drummond allegedly suffered a leg injury and Johnson an
eye injury.
</P>
<P>
Hide denied assaulting them and claimed Johnson had later
telephoned him and offered to drop the allegations for 30,000
Pounds(about 50,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The call had been taped and was passed to police but a voice
expert was unable to identify the voice on the tape.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, a market trader who now lives in Nottingham, failed
to appear for the start of the trial on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The judge was told police attempts to find him had proved
unsuccessful.
</P>
<P>
Charles Kellett, prosecuting, said the boxer should be tried
only on the alleged attack on Drummond and said seven prosecution
witnesses were available to give evidence.
</P>
<P>
But the judge decided the incidents could not be heard
separately.
</P>
<P>
Drummond, a former amateur lightweight boxer, said afterwards
he felt very let down and added: "I don't think justice has been
done.Herbie Hide will never be a true world champion. He is only
a title holder."
</P>
<P>
In December Hide was given a community service order after
being convicted of using threatening behaviour towards two
Norwich policemen who stopped him in his car.
</P>
<P>
The British Boxing Board of Control warned Hide about his
behaviour after that incident but the board's general secretary,
John Morris, declined to comment on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980902.0306 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Tourism to Mainland Increases Despite Economic Slump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Despite the overall slump of
Asian tourism, more than 2.1 million people from Taiwan visited
China's mainland in the first half of this year, a year-on-year
increase of 10 percent, according to the Taiwan Travel Quality
Assurance Association.
</P>
<P>
Xu Jinrui, chairman of the association, said the rise was quite
unexpected by Taiwan travel agencies taking into account the
general market conditions.
</P>
<P>
He made these remarks at a tourism seminar held here recently
by the Guizhou Tourism Bureau and a travel periodical of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan travel agencies who attended the seminar attributed the
growth to improved services of mainland hotels, and more
convenient transportation and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the enhanced promotion by the travel industry in
the central and western regions also helped draw more Taiwanese
tourists.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 million Taiwan people have come to visit the
mainland since home visits were allowed by Taiwan authorities in
1987. In 1997, the number hit a record high of 1.92 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
