<HEADLINE> Canada Announces Contribution to Mines Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Canada Tuesday announced a
contribution of 300,000 Canadian dollars (192,000 U.S.dollars) to
the non-governmental organization, Mines Action Canada, to help
sustain its work and activities in the campaign to ban
anti-personnel mines.
</P>
<P>
"We are within reach of the 40 ratifications necessary to bring
the Ottawa Convention into legal force. The intensive diplomatic
lobbying for this Convention would have meant little without the
tireless efforts of our partners in the non-governmental
organization community," Canadian Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy
said in a release.
</P>
<P>
"Mines Action Canada has been a leader in this coalition and I
am pleased to support their active role in the ongoing work needed
to eliminate these deadly weapons," added the Minister.
</P>
<P>
The contribution will be sourced from Canada's
100-million-Canadian-dollar Landmines Fund announced last December
at the international signing conference of the Ottawa Convention.
</P>
