<HEADLINE> Greece Willing to Help Russia Overcome Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Tuesday expressed its
willingness to help Russia overcome the current worsening economic
crisis which has badly affected the world financial markets.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after meeting with President Costis Stephanopoulos,
Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros Pangalos said Tuesday that his
country was prepared to participate in any procedure to help
Russia out of its economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
While pointing out that all European countries were concerned
about Russia's economic crisis, he warned that if the west did not
help Russia, th consequencies would be unpropitious and all would
be forced to pay the cost.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Greek government spokesman Dimitris
Reppas said Tuesday that Athens hoped U.S. President Bill
Clinton's visit to Russia would yield results for the Russian
economy.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the Russian government needed to implement
changes to the country's banking and tax system. 
