<HEADLINE> International Religions Meeting Ends in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The three-day "People and
Religions" International Ecumenical Meeting ended here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the closing session, Romania's President Emil
Constantinescu noted,"The gathering has demonstrated once more
that the dialogue remains the only efficient way to get us
together, in order to find out what really unites us."
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu stressed that the experience of this dialogue
proves that politics and religion can well gather for the common
good.
</P>
<P>
"In this process of re-establishing the world order, religions
can remind some essential truths we very often neglect: the truth
that life is sacred and the beauty of the human being springs the
most from its fragility; the truth that we cannot complete
ourselves without help from the others," the President added.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the Meeting were more than 800 representatives
of the most important religions of the world.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was organized by Romania's Presidency, the Romanian
Patriarchy and the Sant'Egidio Community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
